-- Broad Helps England Take Control of Cricket Test in New Zealand
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-03-16T15:20:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-16/broad-helps-england-take-control-of-cricket-test-in-new-zealand.html
Stuart Broad’s six-wicket haul
helped  England  take control of the second cricket Test against
New Zealand in Wellington.  Broad was 6-51 as New Zealand was bowled out for 254 on day
three in response to England’s first innings 465. The host was
then forced to follow on, reaching 77-1 at stumps at Basin
Reserve to trail by 134 runs.  The series opener in Dunedin ended in a draw, with the
final Test beginning March 22 in Auckland.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  